SIMPLE: looking
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Looking
<hw>Look"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a certain look or
appearance; -- often compounded with adjectives; <as>as,
good<ex>-looking</ex>, grand<ex>-looking</ex>, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Looking</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Looking
<hw>Look"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who
looks; a glance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The manner in which one looks; appearance;
countenance; face.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All dreary was his cheer and his <qex>looking</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Looking for</b></col>, <cd>anticipation;
expectation.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧A certain fearful <xex>looking for</xex> of
judgment.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Heb. x. 27.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Looking-glass</ent>⟦br⟧
